  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Jon Stewart has not announced any plans to run for president. Stewart, known for his work as a comedian, political commentator, and former host of *The Daily Show*, has often been the subject of speculation about a potential political career. However, he has repeatedly downplayed the idea of running for office, expressing a preference for advocacy and using his platform to influence public discourse rather than seeking elected office.\n\nThat said, political ambitions can change, and Stewart's influence and popularity mean that any announcement from him about running for president would generate significant attention. For now, though, there is no official indication that he plans to enter the race. If you're curious about his activities, keeping an eye on his public statements or projects (like his advocacy work for veterans and 9/11 first responders) might provide insight into his future plans.",
